rest_of_day_open: i see it going ok, i have a paper due Monday and next Thursday and I haven't even started it LOL so if I can get through it it will be good if I cant then it will be bad. I'm hoping it ends up being good for my sakes
critical_positive: the guy knew how to keep a conversation going. I've had some dry conversations and some good conversations here and he ranks among the best. i don't even know if we have anything really in common but he just seemed like the type of person anyone could get along with
critical_negative: there wasnt anything really that didnt work well in the conversation. sometimes I would try to interject while he was talking which would be a normal thing in a face to face conversation but I feel like when you're doing It over video chat as soon as someone interjects you automatically stop what you're saying instead of what you do in a normal face to face conversation of hearing what the person says and continuing the conversation

begin_memory_text: We talked about him having to drive 3 hours to get to his girlfriend's parents house. He was there to do the chat. He showed me his girlfriend's old bedroom that had a lot of Marilyn Monroe memorabilia.
middle_memory_text: We talked about COVID and how it effected his work place. He only has to go into work 3 days out of the week. He is an essential worker at a school.
end_memory_text: I talked about my dilemma whether to move back to my parents to save money or to just stay in NYC the whole time. He advises that I move back home to save money. He also talked about how he thinks this chat has something to do with research for computers and software.
rest_of_day_open: Hopefully my friend will come back from Philadelphia on Monday with 3 vegan cheesesteaks that I requested. That would be great. I've been craving them. I'll check on a neighborhood stray cat that had injured its front leg to see if it's getting better. I will also try to be productive and fix up some winter cat shelters.
critical_positive: We were both relaxed and went with the flow of conversation. We lived on the opposite end of the country so we asked each other how both coasts were handling COVID. It was easy to transition into talking about Mexico since he was close to the border. We aren't awkward people so that helped.
critical_negative: I think we had a great and easy conversation. We could have talked for another few minutes, but I felt bad for keeping him since he was doing the chat from his girlfriend's parents house. He had to take the time out from his girlfriend and her family to get online.
